title: Record Rainfall Douses Charleston, South Carolina, as People Rescued Out of Flood Waters
description: The National Weather Service reported that 3.63 inches of rain doused downtown Charleston on Saturday, shattering the one-day record.

title: U.S. Forces Fly in to Embassy in Haiti to Evacuate Nonessential Personnel
description: The U.S. military said it had flown in forces to beef up security at the U.S. Embassy in Haiti and allow nonessential personnel to leave.

title: Why Ramadan Is a Time of Activism for Many Muslims
description: “If Ramadan isn’t a month of activism, I don't know what is,” says Hassan Selim, the Imam of the Islamic Center of Cedar Rapids.

title: King Charles III Awards Brother Prince Edward With Top Honor to Mark His 60th Birthday
description: King Charles III awarded his younger brother, Prince Edward, the Duke of Edinburgh, with a special honor to mark his 60th birthday.

title: West Virginia Lawmakers OK Bill Drawing Back One of the Strictest Child Vaccination Laws
description: West Virginia Lawmakers voted to allow some students who don't attend public schools to be exempt from state vaccination requirements.

title: Kate Middleton Breaks Silence Post-Surgery With a Public Message and New Family Photo
description: Kate Middleton has broken her silence post-surgery with a picture and a message for the public on U.K. Mother’s Day.

title: How Psychedelics Could Help Soldiers Overcome Trauma
description: The U.S. is studying the effects of psychedelic therapy on soldiers with PTSD. Other countries, like Ukraine, are doing similar research.
